This paper deals with a content-centric mobile ad hoc network, which involves communication and information theory aspects (cs.NI, cs.IT). The study focuses on the trade-offs between throughput and delay, which are important performance metrics in distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses caching strategies, which are relevant to information retrieval and storage (cs.SI). Finally, the study involves numerical evaluation and performance comparisons, which are common in multimedia systems and applications (cs.MM).
